Gauteng Health MEC, Bandile Masuku is promising to tackle the challenges faced by patients and employees at Mamelodi Hospital. Courtesy of #DSTV403 PRETORIA - Two Mamelodi Hospital doctors are among four staff members implicated after an elderly woman was found shackled to a bench at the facility. READ: Health dept investigates alleged Mamelodi hospital abuse The four have been placed on special leave. They've been asked to explain why they shouldn't be suspended.
Gauteng Health MEC, Bandile Masuku said, "there is a security guard and medical officers, two doctors and a nurse." "Those have been asked to explain why they shouldn't be suspended and investigate further."